<div class="payload-abstract">Full understanding of behavior and experience requires anappreciation of time-dependent patterns. However, traditionalmethods of observational measurement and self-reportingare ill-suited to capturing such patterns. These methodstend to polarize into either macro-level (gist) analyses oflarge swaths of time or micro-level (atomic) analyses ofdiscrete segments. Unfortunately, both approaches miss thecontinuous, dynamic flow of many psychological processes.Specialized methods are needed that can capture such processesas they unfold over time and across dimensions.</div>
