<div class="payload-abstract">Despite the important role that facial expressionsplay in interpersonal communication and our knowledge thatinterpersonal behavior is influenced by social context, nocurrently available facial expression database includes multipleinteracting participants. The Sayette Group Formation Task(GFT) database addresses the need for well-annotated videoof multiple participants during unscripted interactions. Thedatabase includes 172,800 video frames from 96 participantsin 32 three-person groups. To aid in the development ofautomated facial expression analysis systems, GFT includesexpert annotations of FACS occurrence and intensity, faciallandmark tracking, and baseline results for linear SVM, deeplearning, active patch learning, and personalized classification.Baseline performance is quantified and compared using identicalpartitioning and a variety of metrics (including meansand confidence intervals). The highest performance scores werefound for the deep learning and active patch learning methods.Learn more at http://osf.io/7wcyz.</div>
